#if soper
nickserv/set_strictaccess
#endif
Help for SET STRICTACCESS:

SET STRICTACCESS, if enabled, will mean it's only possible to
identify/login to the account from connections from hosts
listed in the NickServ ACCESS list.  Do NOT enable this
feature unless you know what you are doing.

Syntax: SET STRICTACCESS ON|OFF

Example:
    /msg &nick& SET STRICTACCESS ON
    /msg &nick& SET STRICTACCESS OFF